<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="57.[189,495,641,667]" box="[189,495,641,667]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,495,641,667]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,495,641,667]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Distribution and biology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="57.[189,1399,688,856]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
Collected together with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2015" box="[476,844,688,714]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="index" subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[476,844,688,714]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Sphegina (Asiosphegina) index</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2015" box="[903,1086,688,715]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malaisei" subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[903,1086,688,715]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">S. (A.) malaisei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a Malaise trap near the Tram Ton Pass, the highest mountain pass in 
<collectingCountry box="[713,812,723,749]" name="Vietnam" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(
<quantity box="[827,919,723,749]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" unit="m" value="1900.0">1900 m</quantity>
), near Fan Si Pan mountain. The Malaise trap had been set up in an area of montane forest disturbed by buffaloes grazing, containing muddy areas and small streams. Despite the cold and wet weather insects were still rather abundantly flying (C. van Achterberg, pers. comm).
</paragraph>
